<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Holiday" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Holiday,</orth> a day of exemption from labour, a festival: <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 82</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 82</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.228" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 73</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>holy day</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 86</bibl>. <cit><quote>he speaks h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 69</bibl></cit> (in elegant and choice expressions); cf. <cit><quote>with many h. and lady terms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a h. fool,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h. foolery,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I am in a h. humour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 69</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>